related_items.title: Hermann Göring's activities, January 1-January 17, 1937
description: 1 album (ca. 225 photographic prints) ; 43 x 37 cm. (album) | Photographs show Hermann Goring's visit to horse farm and hunting trip to Rominten. Includes views of Göring's new year inspection of Wehrmacht troops. Also includes views of Göring's birthday celebrations with visits from Roswitha Hueber, staff secretary Victor Lutze and parade of S.A. honor guard and special troops. Also inspection of gifts from the regional government of Braunschweig and meeting other ministers and Nazi party members. Includes views of the Göring's trip to Rome. Includes views of wreath laying ceremony at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier, at St. Peter's Basilica, in the city and arrival and view at the Forum Mussolini. Includes views with Mussolini, Count and Countess Ciano and views with Mussolini at a fencing school. Also includes views of the Göring's as guest at a concert and at a reception. Also includes views of a hunting trip at Castell Porziana, summer residence of King Vittorio Emanuel III. Also includes views of Göring giving speech to group of Germans living in Rome.
